# Force LF for shell scripts regardless of the checking-out platform's
# core.autocrlf setting. Windows' autocrlf=true silently corrupts shebang
# lines in vendored shell scripts (e.g.
# third_party/sqlite-jdbc/amalgamation_version.sh) into
# "#!/usr/bin/env bash\r", which then fails to find a binary named "bash\r".
*.sh text eol=lf
